Package org.goplanit.osm.tags

Class OsmRailwayTags

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.goplanit.osm.tags.OsmRailwayTags
  • public class OsmRailwayTags
extends Object
    Most OSM rail way tags that could be of value for a network. Based on list found on https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:railway. Tags specific to the Ptv1 scheme are collected via the OsmPtv1 tags class and integrated in the collections managed by this class.
    Author:
    markr

      • isAreaBasedRailway

        public static boolean isAreaBasedRailway​(String railwayTagValue)
        Some rail based ways can be areas when tagged in a certain way. currently we do this for both stations and platforms although technically platforms can be ways, but since we do not model them (as ways), we regard them as areas in all cases for now
        Parameters:
        railwayTagValue - the way
        Returns:
        is the way an area and not a line based railway

      • isNonRailBasedRailway

        public static boolean isNonRailBasedRailway​(String railwayTagValue)
        Some railways are in fact valid railway value tags but do not represent a rail track. any such value tags that our parser is aware of can be verified through this method using the NON_RAILBASED_OSM_RAILWAY_VALUE_TAGS
        Parameters:
        railwayTagValue - the way
        Returns:
        is the way an area and not a line based railway
